Below is r code to create plot

```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = 
               aes(x = displ, 
                   y = hwy), 
             alpha = .5) + 
  facet_wrap( class ~ .)
```


```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = 
               aes(x = displ, 
                   y = hwy), 
             alpha = .5) + 
  facet_wrap( class ~ . , ncol = 2)

```
~ is used for =
## Overplotting Issues
drv shows which type of driving it is and cyl is the cylinders
```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = 
               aes(x = displ, 
                   y = hwy),
             alpha = .5) + 
  facet_grid(drv ~ cyl)
```


## Section 2
classwork 6 question 3
```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy),
             alpha = .5) +
  facet_grid(drv ~ .)

ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy),
             alpha = .5) +
  facet_grid(. ~ cyl)
```


q3b
```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = drv, y = cyl))
```
```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = drv, y = cyl))


```


No column split if . is used
facet_grid(Row wise split~ column wise split)
makes facet ignore corresponding split
```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy),
             alpha = .5) +
  facet_grid(drv ~ .)

ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy),
             alpha = .5) +
  facet_grid(. ~ drv)

```
ggplot divides scatter plot using other variables
disadvantage of facet is that it takes more effort to see each subplot

```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy),
             alpha = .5) + 
  facet_wrap(~ class, nrow = 2)

```


```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color=class),
             alpha = .5  ) +
  facet_wrap(~ class, nrow = 2)

```
Whenever a variable has a decimal point it is fair to assume that its continuous

```{r}
ggplot( data=tvshows) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x=GRP, y=PE),alpha=.5) +
  facet_wrap( Genre ~ .) +
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x=GRP, y=PE))


```
use geom point and geom smooth together

```{r}
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_histogram(mapping = 
                aes(x = displ, binwidth = 3))

```











